5
00:00:32,780 --> 00:00:35,010
won&#39;t proceed as normal.

6
00:00:35,010 --> 00:00:39,969
We concluded that there was not a critical period for attachment in human development,

7
00:00:39,969 --> 00:00:44,860
because children could overcome early deprivation, and come to have attachment relationships

8
00:00:44,860 --> 00:00:50,170
with people even after they didn&#39;t have an opportunity to have a single attachment figure

9
00:00:50,170 --> 00:00:52,950
in the first few years of life.

10
00:00:52,950 --> 00:00:56,980
As you&#39;ll see with language development, it seems to be a bit of a different story.

11
00:00:56,980 --> 00:01:01,520
