18
00:01:30,060 --> 00:01:31,549
is spoken language.

19
00:01:31,549 --> 00:01:36,689
But in some cases, it&#39;ll be sign language if you&#39;ve got people who have hearing impairment

20
00:01:36,689 --> 00:01:40,180
or can&#39;t produce noises from their larynx.

21
00:01:40,180 --> 00:01:46,560
Languages differ all across the world, but, every human group known has a language.

22
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:51,240
Not only that, if you look at every human group and their children, you&#39;ll find that

23
00:01:51,240 --> 00:01:57,130
the children show an extraordinarily regular developmental progression for language.

24
00:01:57,130 --> 00:02:01,219
Children tend to say their first word around their first birthdays.

25
00:02:01,219 --> 00:02:07,260
After a period of producing single word utterances, they start stringing words together.

26
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:12,350
When they start to do that, they follow grammatical rules without ever having been explicitly

27
00:02:12,350 --> 00:02:13,720
taught.

28
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:18,889
And by the time they&#39;re between four and five years old, children are producing utterances

29
00:02:18,889 --> 00:02:23,920
that are basically as long as the utterances of fully fluent speakers of the language.

